Made a much needed, big upgrade to our boat this year. We replaced our pre existing lead acid batteries with all @x2powerbattery lithium ion batteries with the exception of one AGM house/cranking battery. 

Why did we do this? 

Because it’s omitting approximately 83 pounds of added weight to our aluminum boat which is a lot. Performance wise, our boat is going to perform a lot better, increasing our overall battery time and life while on the water while also adding a bonus few extra MPH. 😎

I often get asked what my favorite fishing technique is and here it is: 👇🏻

I’m a huge fan fishing with light tackle, especially drop shot during the summer months. I love a weedless drop shot presentation for fishing weed edges and isolated weed areas without the hassle of getting snagged with an exposed hook. The @berkleyfishing Max Scent D Worm is the perfect bait for this technique. The D Worm has a super natural presentation when rigged this way. It also excels on a shaky head which I also throw a lot during this time of year. 

I pair it with the @fenwickfishing techna spinning rod (medium/light) and the @pfluegerproducts Patriarch Spinning Reel and I always use hi-vis Berkley (Fire Line) braid to fluoro. I like being able to see my line move in the water. Questions? I’m happy to answer them. 
.
.

It’s been a very long time since I’ve introduced myself…. 

Thank you to my followers who have stuck around and have gotten to know me and followed my journey over the years…

My name is Andrea, born and raised in a what was (once) a small town in Connecticut. In November, I’ll be celebrating my last year in my 30’s. I will not be crying tears of joy the day I turn 40. 😆 

I have two kids who are my world. We fish, explore and garden together. There’s nothing more rewarding than my children enjoying the hobbies that I’m passionate about. 

I am a diehard Republican woman with strong conservative views. 🇺🇸 

I started fishing and hunting at a very young age. It’s the thing I’m post passionate about and makes me the happiest. I’m an ambassador for some of the best companies in the business including @dsgfish which takes women’s outdoor/fishing apparel to a whole new level @berkleyfishing and @abugarcia_fishing for rods/reels and fishing tackle and @x2powerbattery for powering our boat with the best lithium batteries out there and helping us make the most of the time we have on the water. 

Over the last two years or so I’ve really gotten into gardening and canning. It’s truly rewarding to be able to feed my family on food we’ve grown and harvested ourselves. 

I was a Paramedic for a long time. I have seen things nobody should ever have to see but I am grateful I was able to help so many people during my career. I am still licensed but that chapter of my life is closed. 

I have been a stay at home mom the last five years until this summer. I recently started my own lawn mowing business. Super psyched about being my own boss and the flexibility of having my own schedule. Ideal actually. 🤩 I’ve always loved labor intensive work and instant gratification. Freshly manicured lawns is all of that for me. 

Thanks again for sticking around! Love you all!

What a weekend. Prep was exceptionally challenging for this fair because it’s so late in the season and the selections of some of my tomato varieties were limited. Some how though, I was able to harvest enough impressive varieties for my “collection” to win Best in Show at the 166th Annual @harwintonfair. My raspberry jam took another first place win which is three fairs in a row for that variety.  It’s crazy to me to see where I ended up vs. where I started. 

This has been my first year participating in showing veggies and putting some of my canning projects on display and I’m so glad I did. This has been a blast. 

Shout out to @the.jayniv for winning first place on his pumpkin this weekend too. So much work goes into growing big pumpkins. We really enjoyed watching the crowds of people taking photos with them over the duration of the fair weekend. 🎃 #gardening #countryfair #tomatoes #canning #fair #garden #vegetables
